  <Subject Subject_ID="300042339">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300209194</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>lip-vibrated aerophones with cylindrical bore [300209194], lip-vibrated aerophones [300041639], aerophones [300041622], sound devices by acoustical characteristics [300041621], sound devices (equipment) [300387677], Sound Devices (hierarchy name) [300041619], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Generally, all lip-vibrated aerophones of predominantly cylindrical bore.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>En general, todos los aerófonos que vibran con los labios de diámetro interior predominantemente cilíndrico. Puede también referirse específicamente a las trompetas de bandas, de concierto y orquestas modernas occidentales, con una ancha boquilla, un diámetro interior estrecho, válvulas, y una campana de cuello y contorno expandido de tamaño mediano.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In algemene zin: alle blaasinstrumenten, bespeeld door lipspanning, en meestal met cylindrische boring. In specifieke zin: blaasinstrumenten in moderne westerse context met een wijd mondstuk, smalle boring, kleppen en een middelgrote klankhals en klankbeker.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052452/Encyclopedie van muziekinstrumenten (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Geralmente, todos os aerofones vibram com os lábios de diâmetro predominantemente cilíndrico. Também pode se referir especificamente à banda ocidental moderna, concerto e trompetes orquestrais, tendo um bocal largo, um orifício estreito, válvulas e uma garganta de sino de tamanho médio e sino de alargamento.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Allgemein jedes Lippenton-Aerofon mit zylindrischer Röhre. Die Bezeichnung kann sich auch spezifischer auf moderne westliche Konzerttrompeten oder Orchestertrompeten beziehen, die ein weites Mundstück, eine enge Röhre, Ventile und einen mittelgroßen Schalltrichter haben.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
